extends layout

block content
  .row
    .col-md-6
      .card
        .card-body
            .mb-3
                h5.font-weight-semibold.mb-
                    a.text-default(href='#') Blog post #4 title
                ul.list-inline.list-inline-dotted.mb-3
                    li.list-inline-item
                        | By 
                        a(href='#') Eugene
                    li.list-inline-item July 5th, 2016
                    li.list-inline-item
                        a(href='#') 12 comments
                    li.list-inline-item
                        a(href='#')
                            i.icon-heart6.font-size-base.text-pink.mr-2
                            |  281
            p.mb-3
                | One morning, when Gregor Samsa woke from troubled dreams, he found himself transformed in his bed into a horrible vermin. He lay on his armour-like back, and if he lifted his head a little he could see his brown belly, slightly domed and divided by arches into stiff sections.
            blockquote.blockquote.blockquote-bordered.py-2.pl-3.mb-0
                p.mb-2.font-size-base
                    | When suspiciously goodness labrador understood rethought yawned grew piously endearingly inarticulate oh goodness jeez trout distinct hence cobra.
                footer.blockquote-footer
                    | Jason, 
                    cite(title='Source Title') 10:39 am
        .card-footer.d-flex.justify-content-between.align-items-center.py-2
            ul.list-inline.mb-0
                li.list-inline-item
                    a.d-flex.align-items-center(href='#')
                        span.position-relative
                            img.rounded-circle(src='/global_assets/images/placeholders/placeholder.jpg', width='32', height='32', alt='')
                            span.badge.badge-mark.badge-float.border-danger.mt-1.mr-1
                        span.ml-2 Eugene Kopyov
            a(href='/read-artilce')
                | Full article 
                i.icon-circle-right2.ml-2


